In this article, President Donald Trump issues a proclamation for World Trade Week, emphasizing the importance of free, fair, and reciprocal trade for American and global prosperity. He reaffirms the commitment to ensuring that farmers, ranchers, manufacturers, and entrepreneurs can sell their goods and services in the global market on a level playing field. Trump highlights the economic success of his administration, including the creation of new jobs and a growing GDP. He acknowledges that economic aggression and unfair trading practices of other countries have hampered American prosperity, but his administration is using all available tools to confront these practices. Trump mentions efforts to modernize and improve trade agreements, renegotiating deals like the United States-Korea Free Trade Agreement (KORUS) and the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) to benefit American workers. He also mentions negotiations with other countries to secure broader market access for American products and services. Trump concludes by emphasizing the importance of free, fair, balanced, and reciprocal trade for the United States and its trading partners, and encourages Americans to observe World Trade Week.